title: Vaccination coverage in children in the United Kingdom
analysis_commentary: In 2013/14, there was a high percentage of children (>93%) in the United Kingdom completing the recommended immunisations by the age of two years, with little variation between the four nations across all vaccines.
data_source: Public Health England, Cover of vaccination evaluated rapidly programme <https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/vaccine-uptake>
